<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata Pledges To Achieve Tax Reform This Year </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Pledges To Achieve Tax Reform This Year </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006235294 Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 10 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1006235294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo ASAHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On the issue of achieving a drastic reform of the 
tax system by the end of the year, Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
declared in the House of Councillors' Budget Committee session 
on 9 June that passing the related legislation is a public 
commitment of his administration: "Without a doubt, this is a 
public commitment. I also think it will be an important 
historic event." 
  Hata's remarks came in reply to a question posed by 
Toranosuke Katayama of the Liberal Democratic Party, who asked, 
"Is it correct to say that you are making a public commitment to 
formulating the legislation by the end of June and having the 
Diet pass it by the end of the year?" Asked about the political 
responsibility he might assume in case of failing to achieve the 
reform, however, Hata only said, "I want to tackle the issue 
seriously." 

</TEXT>

