<F P=100> SOUTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Burma </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senior General Than Shwe, Delegation Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senior General Than Shwe, Delegation Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306154694 Rangoon Radio Burma in Burmese 1330 GMT 13 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1306154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rangoon Radio Burma </F>
<F P=105>  Burmese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Senior General Than Shwe, chairman of the State Law 
and Order Restoration Council [SLORC] of the Union of Myanmar 
[Burma], arrived back in Yangon [Rangoon] by special aircraft at 
0915. They were on a goodwill visit to the Lao People's 
Democratic Republic [LPDR] at the invitation of the Laotian 
president, Mr. Nouhak Phoumsavan. Sr. Gen. Than Shwe was 
accompanied by his wife Daw Kyaing Kyaing. 
  They were welcomed at Yangon airport by General Maung Aye, 
vice chairman of SLORC; Vice Admiral Maung Maung Khin and 
Lieutenant General Tin Tun, SLORC members and deputy prime 
ministers; Lt. Gen. Tin U, SLORC secretary-2, and SLORC members; 
cabinet ministers; deputy foreign minister, senior military 
officers and their wives; responsible military and civil 
officials; Dr. Baron Walther von Bieberstein, German ambassador 
and dean of diplomatic corps; ambassadors, charge d'affairs, and 
their wives; and Mrs. (Virasak Bunsak), charge d'affaires of 
LPDR. 
  Sr. Gen. Than Shwe and his wife were also accompanied by 
Lieutenant General Khin Nyunt, SLORC secretary-1, and his wife, 
Dr. Khin Win Shwe; Lt. Gen. Myint Aung, minister of agriculture; 
Brigadier General Abel, minister of national planning and 
economic development; U Ohn Gyaw, minister of foreign affairs, 
and wife; Brig. Gen. Myo Thant, minister of information; and 
responsible personnel from the SLORC office, Defense Ministry, 
and Foreign Ministry. 

</TEXT>

