<H3> <TI>   Hun Sen Told of Need To Ease Investments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hun Sen Told of Need To Ease Investments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406071694 Phnom Penh AKP in French 0427 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1406071694 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh 14 Jun (AKP) -- Mr. Chin Siat Yoon, 
Singaporean ambassador to Cambodia, emphasized the need to 
faciliate the investments of Singaporean companies in Cambodia. 
  Singapore's diplomat was received by Samdech Hun Sen, second 
prime minister of the Royal Government, in Phnom Penh on 10 
June. Bilateral cooperation and especially Singapore's 
investments in Cambodia were at the center of the discussions. 
  Mr. Chin Siat Yoon disclosed the commitment of his 
government 
to help Cambodia achieve economic development. 
  "Cambodia must strengthen its cooperation with Singapore, 
declared Samdech Hun Sen, particularly in the construction of an 
airport and a port." Scholarships on management training will 
be given by Singapore to future personnel of these projects. 
  The second prime minister informed his guest of the current 
situation in Cambodia, assuring him that the government is 
capable of maintaining security in the country. 

</TEXT>

