<H3> <TI>   NADK Reports`Control' of Nine Villages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NADK Reports`Control' of Nine Villages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406020294 (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia in Cambodian 2330 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1406020294 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Voice of the Great National Union 
Front of Cambodia </F>

<F P=105>  Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 11 June the people and the National Army of 
Democratic Kampuchea [NADK] swept the invading forces of the 
two-headed government from Toek Chum commune to Spean Treng and 
from Prasat commune to Phnum Liep commune in Preah Net Preah 
District, Battambang Province. We completely liberated and and 
now control this area including the following nine villages: 
Rouch, Spean, Toek Chum, Cha, Kouk Siem, Toek Haoch, Aumal, 
Anlung Cha, and Bat Trang. 
  We killed or wounded a number of enemy soldiers and seized 
15 
assorted firearms and a quantity of ammunition and war materiel. 
  The people also joined hands in destroying the Phnum Liep 
bridge to deprive the communist Vietnamese puppets and 
two-headed government of its use for transporting troops and 
ammunition in their operations to persecute, kill, and rob the 
local people. 

</TEXT>

