<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   King Asks To Have Sick Prisoners Released </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    King Asks To Have Sick Prisoners Released </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306114194 Phnom Penh AKP in English 1001 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1306114194 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh AKP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Phnom Penh AKP June 13 -- His Majesty King Norodom 
Sihanouk has asked the government to release women and sick 
prisoners from its jails. 
  In his statement dated on June 10 and faxed from his 
residence in Beijing to the Cambodian co-premiers the king said, 
  "this current report brings me to ask that you free, for 
humanitarian reasons, the very sick prisoners and more 
particularly those who, in general, have not committed serious 
crimes or violent crimes". 
  "Many defendants who are particularly impoverished, notably 
the women, have stagnated in preventative detention for months 
or even years awaiting judgement", Sihanouk said in the 
statement, which was dated Friday. 
  Sihanouk said the freeing of sick prisoners would enable the 
country's penal authorities to improve prison conditions while 
waiting to find adequate financial means for the creation of new 
detention centres". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

