<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EAS-94-114 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  13 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Laos </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Minister Leaves for Geneva Conference </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Labor Minister Leaves for Geneva Conference </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306135494 Vientiane KPL in English 0917 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1306135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Vientiane KPL </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vientiane, June 13 (KPL) -- A delegation of the 
Ministry of Labour and Social Welfare of the Lao PDR [Lao 
People's Democratic Republic] led by its minister, Thongloun 
Sisoulit left here on June 11 for Geneva, Switzerland, to attend 
the annual conference of the International Labour Organization 
to be held there from June 7-24. 
  At this conference, the Council of Labour from each member 
country will make a report on the labour situation of their 
countries. The conference will also discuss many issues 
concerning labour, management and use of labour and labour 
welfare, as well as the protection of the just right of the 
working people. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

