<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cooperation With Malaysia `Strengthening' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cooperation With Malaysia `Strengthening' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406073494 Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network in Tagalog 
0500 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1406073494 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City PTV-4 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Philippines and Malaysia are working at 
strengthening their joint defense cooperation. This was 
revealed by Defense Secretary Renato de Villa after his meeting 
with Malaysian Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak in 
Kuala Lumpur. 
  According to De Villa, Tun Razak proposed the formulation of 
plans for the exchange of defense equipment between the two 
countries. De Villa said he likewise proposed launching joint 
patrol operations to stop high-sea smuggling in the area between 
the Philippines and Malaysia. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

