<H3> <TI>   Further Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reportage on Reaction to DPRK Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Aid to DPRK Considered </H4>

<F P=102> OW1406053894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 14 
Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1406053894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 14 June Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] A top Ministry of Foreign Affairs official said on 
13 June: "If North Korea accepts inspections without fail, we 
can consider that [economic assistance]." He was commenting on 
a reported remark by DPRK (North Korean) President Kim Il-song 
that if cooperation was obtained in the DPRK's normalization of 
relations with the United States, and assistance was provided 
for its efforts to convert [existing nuclear reactors] to light 
water reactors, North Korea would cooperate with International 
Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) inspections. 
  The official said that if North Korea accepted full 
inspections, it would be possible for Japan to consider economic 
aid. 

</TEXT>

