BFN 

<F P=106> [From Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 14 Jun Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] According to a report by delegation members, a 
group of Social Democratic Party of Japan [SDPJ] members met 
Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea [CCWPK] and concurrently chairman of the 
Committee on Foreign Affairs, at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on 
the morning of 13 June. The SDPJ delegation, led by Kazo 
Watanabe, director of the general affairs department of the SDPJ 
Central Executive Committee, is currently visiting the DPRK. 
  Watanabe and other delegation members stressed that the 
issue 
of North Korea's suspected development of nuclear weapons should 
be resolved through dialogue. In response, Hwang reiterated 
North Korea's stand, saying: "We do not plan to possess nuclear 
weapons. We do not have the technology nor the funds necessary 
to develop such weapons." 

