<F P=100> Thailand </F>
<H3> <TI>   Prasong Warns Burmese Not To Protest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prasong Warns Burmese Not To Protest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406063694 Bangkok BANGKOK POST in English 14 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> BK1406063694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok BANGKOK POST </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Prasong Susiri warned Burmese 
students yesterday not to protest in an effort to bar Rangoon's 
representatives from attending a foreign ministers' meeting of 
the Association of Southeast Asian Nations. 
  Burma will attend the ASEAN ministerial meeting in Bangkok 
in 
July for the first time as the guest of the host country, 
Thailand. Sqn Ldr [Squadron Leader] Prasong said dissident 
Burmese students should refrain from conducting political 
activities affecting Thailand's relations with Burma. 
  "The Burmese students who live at the (Burmese Students) 
centre should know how to behave. 
  "It is not appropriate for them to conduct any activities 
jeopardising relations between Thailand and neighbouring 
countries while living here," the minister said, apparently 
referring to Burma. 
  The Interior Ministry is attempting to block protests which 
might take place during the meeting. 
  Interior officials are keeping a watch on Burmese dissidents 
and ethnic minority groups including students at the centre at 
Ban Maniloi in Rat Buri Province as the ministry has been told 
about a plan to prevent Rangoon officials from attending the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

