<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Deep Concern' Expressed Over Nuclear Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Deep Concern' Expressed Over Nuclear Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406114794 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1406114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In answering an AFP correspondent inquiring about 
Vietnam's reaction on the IAEA's [International Atomic Energy 
Agency] decision to pose punitive sanctions on the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea, a spokesman of our Foreign Ministry 
on 14 June said: 
  Vietnam follows with deep concern recent developments of the 
nuclear issue in the Korean Peninsula. We believe that all 
members of the International Atomic Energy Agency, IAEA, have 
similar obligations in the nuclear issue. We are always 
persistent in our belief that the solution for this complicated 
issue can only be reached through resolute and serious 
negotiations between the parties concerned on the basis of 
equality and respect to each other's independence and 
sovereignty and to international laws. 
  All actions at variance with that direction will only worsen 
the already complicated situation, and will harm the trend of 
peace, stability, and cooperation for the Pacific region which 
all countries in the region are striving to maintain. 

</TEXT>

