<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Papua New Guinea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government, Secessionists Sign Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government, Secessionists Sign Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306055694 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1306055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Progress towards a negotiated peace in Bougainville 
is reported to have taken a step forward with representatives of 
the Papua New Guinea [PNG] government and the secessionists 
signing an agreement to hold further talks soon. The agreement 
was reached at talks in Honiara hosted by Solomon Islands Prime 
Minister Francis Billy Hilly. Among those attending the meeting 
were the secretary to PNG's prime minister, (Brown Bau), and the 
secessionist international representative, (Moses Havini). 
  Sources in the Solomon Islands Government said the meeting 
paved the way for a summit conference of Bougainville leaders 
representing both the secessionists and the PNG Government in 
Honiara next week. Solomon Islands radio said the summit will be 
part of the consultative process to establish dialogue in the 
lead up to proposed Pan-Bougainville peace conference. 

</TEXT>

