Japanese 0300 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW1406035494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NHK General Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video; from the "NHK News" </F>
program] 
  [Text] Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata expressed his serious 
regrets at the House of Councillors' Budget Committee this 
morning on North Korea's (the DPRK's) announcement of its 
withdrawal from the IAEA (International Atomic Energy Agency). 
He indicated that he would continue to persist in persuading 
North Korea to agree to hold dialogue with the international 
community. 
  [Begin Hata recording] With regard to the withdrawal from 
IAEA, it is indeed unfortunate. However, this still does not 
mean withdrawal from the nuclear NPT [Nonproliferation Treaty]. 
In the circumstances, we still hold hopes that they [the North 
Koreans] will open their doors to the international community as 
soon as possible to eliminate suspicions about their development 
of nuclear weapons. [end recording] 
  Hata thus indicated his intention to persist in persuading 
North Korea to engage in dialogue with the international 
community. 

</TEXT>

