<H3> <TI>   DPRK on Tokyo `Preparing SDF' Against North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK on Tokyo `Preparing SDF' Against North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1406074594 Tokyo KYODO in English 0713 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1406074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- North Korea accused Japan 
on Tuesday of preparing to dispatch Self Defense Force (SDF) 
troops to the Korean Peninsula under the guise of "collective 
security measures" according to a report from Pyongyang 
monitored in Tokyo. 
  The Korean Central News Agency (KCNA) dispatch said that an 
analyst for NODONG SINMUN, the Korean Workers' Party newspaper, 
accused Japan of zealously joining the United States in its 
efforts to force North Korea to agree to international 
inspections of its nuclear facilities. 
  The analyst warned that if international sanctions were 
imposed on North Korea, Japan would dispatch SDF personnel to 
the Korean peninsula. "This indicates Japan's hostile policy 
(toward North Korea) is reaching the extreme," the analyst said. 
  The KCNA report was monitored by the Korea News Service, a 
Tokyo-based agency watching developments on the peninsula. 

</TEXT>

