<F P=100> NORTHEAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata To Urge Continued Western Aid for Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata To Urge Continued Western Aid for Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1406033994 Tokyo KYODO in English 0323 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1406033994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
indicated Tuesday [14 Jun] he will appeal for continued aid to 
Russia, eastern Europe and South Africa when he meets leaders of 
the Group of Seven (G-7) industrial nations at the Naples summit 
in July. 
  Hata told the House of Councillors Budget Committee the 
developing countries would have serious difficulty in solving 
their various problems if the G-7 discontinued its aid. 
  Britain, Canada, France, Germany, Italy, Japan and the 
United 
States are scheduled to take part in the summit. 

</TEXT>

