<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Agency Plans Management Lecture in SRV </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1306055194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0500 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1306055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Osaka, June 13 KYODO -- The Pacific Resource 
Exchange Center, a government-backed agency, will dispatch its 
officials to Vietnam to lecture on corporate management and 
other issues, center officials said Monday [13 Jun]. 
  The lecture, to be held June 14-24 in Ho Chi Minh city and 
Hanoi, is designed to help Vietnam smoothly shift to a market 
economy under its "doi moi" reform policy. 
  The economic reform has engendered a number of problems, 
such 
as a widening gap in the living standards between big cities and 
other areas and deteriorating health of state-run enterprises. 
  The planned lecture will focus on ways to nurture and 
strengthen managerially weak small firms and breathe new life 
into economically backward local areas. 

</TEXT>

