<H3> <TI>   Tokyo To Provide $9 Million Emergency Aid to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Tokyo To Provide $9 Million Emergency Aid to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006011094 Tokyo KYODO in English 0022 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006011094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 10 KYODO -- Japan will extend emergency 
aid totaling 9 million dollars to international organizations to 
help the victims of the conflict in Rwanda, the Foreign Ministry 
said Friday [10 June]. 
  The aid consists of 6.45 million dollars to the UN High 
Commissioner for Refugees, 2.4 million dollars to the 
International Committee of the Red Cross and 150,000 dollars to 
the World Health Organization, the ministry said. 
  The conflict in Rwanda has been expanding and intensifying 
since disputes erupted between government and anti-government 
troops in early April. The ministry quoted UN sources as saying 
more than 500,000 people have died as a result of the fighting 
and massacres, while about 3 million people have either left 
their homes or fled to Tanzania, Burundi, Zaire and Uganda. 
  But despite efforts by humanitarian organizations, the 
victims of the conflict are in disastrous condition because of 
the lack of food, drinking water and medical goods, the ministry 
said. 

</TEXT>

