<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Cut Base Lending Rate by 0.2 Percent </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To Cut Base Lending Rate by 0.2 Percent </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1306055294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0449 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1306055294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 13 KYODO -- The Finance Ministry will 
cut the base rate on lending to government affiliates by 0.20 
percentage point to an annual 4.10 percent, effective Friday [17 
Jun], ministry said Monday. 
  The move reflected recent declines in the coupon on 
long-term 
government bonds, the officials said. 
  Given the rate reduction, the ministry will consult with the 
Construction Ministry to decide on new rates on public loans 
extended by Housing Loan Corp. 
  The new base rate, for example, on loans for purchasing 
newly 
built housing with floor space of up to 125 square meters, is 
expected to go down by 0.15 percentage point to an annual 3.90 
percent, effective the same day. 
  The base rates on public housing loans link with those on 
lending by Finance Ministry's Trust Fund Bureau by using funds 
of the fiscal investment and loan program. 
  The current housing loan rates of 4.05 percent were set on 
April 22 after a round of rate hikes from an all-time low of 
3.60 percent marked on Jan. 26. 

</TEXT>

