<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Carries Press Reviews </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    MONTSAME Carries Press Reviews </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    For 11 Jun </H4>

<F P=102> BK1206121494 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1026 GMT 11 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1206121494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 11 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The official 
Newspaper "ARDIYN ERH" informs that at the siting here spring 
session of the Great State Hural of Mongolia it has been decided 
to celebrate on 26 November of the current year the 70th jubilee 
of the approval of the first constitution of Mongolia and 
declaration of independence of the republic. The Mongolian 
parliament is to take a special bill on this point later. Also 
an organizational committee has been set up to provide 
preparations and arrangement of the measures for the occasion of 
the jubilee under the guidance of the chairman of the Great 
State Hural N. Bagabandi. The session of the parliament started 
debating the draft law on pension and benefits relating to 
servicemen at the second reading. 
  The newspaper informs that at the closed sitting of the 
Mongolian parliament the legislators have discussed and approved 
the proposal by the Mongolbank on issuing into circulation of 
new 5,000 and 10,000 tugrik banknotes and coins of 20, 50, 100, 
200 values. 
  In its traditional heading "From Dawn to Dusk" the newspaper 
carries some information concerning the latest events and 
development occurred in the country. It is reported on the 
forum of young members and supporters of the ruling Mongolian 
People's Revolutionary Party, the participation of Mongolian 
sportsmen in the annual international tournament in judo 
wrestling held in the city Krasnoyarsk Russian Federation. 
  The newspaper also provides an interview of its 
correspondent 
with the first secretary of the Embassy of Denmark to Beijing 
Ole Odgaar. 
  The talk was about the assistance being provided to Mongolia 
by the Danish "Danida" organization. A permanent representative 
of the Danida would be working at the Ministry of Food and 
Agriculture of Mongolia. This Danish organization has granted 
to Mongolia gratis aid of 1.6 million US dollars to be assigned 
for the purposes referring to prophylaxis and another 1.5 
million US dollars for acquiring fertilizers necessary and 
combating harmful incests. 
  In connection with the presupposed submitting for 
consideration to the Great State Hural of the draft law on state 
security the newspaper informs about the actions of secret 
services on state security of India, United States of America, 
Japan, Germany and Russia. 
  The newspaper also gives an interview with retired General 
B. 
Tsiyregdzen who was at the head of the body on social security 
of the country during the period from 1984 to 1990. 
  Concerning the international affairs the newspaper reports 
about the forthcoming visit to the United States of America of 
Emperor of Japan Akihito and the official visit of the Minister 
of Foreign Affairs of the People's Republic of China Qian Qichen 
to be paid to the Russian Federation by late June of the year. 
  The governmental newspaper "DZASGIYN GADZRYN MEUEE" 
publishes 
the decree of the government on some measures to be provided for 
the implementation of the national programme for decreasing the 
impoverishment of the population. The newspaper reports on the 
round table talk held here concerning the issues of education. 
The talk was attended by rector of the state pedagogical 
university, Doctor Prof. B. Chuluundorj, director of the 
Technical University N. Tsend, Doctor B. Dabaasuren and other 
scholars discussing the issues of concern facing in the sphere 
of education. 

</TEXT>

