<H3> <TI>   DPRK Warned </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Warned </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406015294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0139 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406015294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 14 (YONHAP) -- South Korea warned North 
Korea Tuesday against deepening the nuclear crisis, voicing 
serious concern at Pyongyang's announced withdrawal from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA). "The government 
expresses serious concern at North Korea's announcement that it 
will withdraw from the IAEA in retaliation for the IAEA Board of 
Governors' recent sanctions resolution against North Korea," 
Foreign Ministry spokesman Chang Ki-ho said in a statement. 
  "The government warns North Korea against worsening the 
situation regarding the nuclear problem," he said. Pyongyang 
should know that the international community will take a harder 
line through a U.N. Security Council sanctions resolution if 
North Korea fails to comply with all IAEA inspections as a party 
to the Nuclear Non-proliferation Treaty (NPT), he said. 
  "The government advises that North Korea accept the will of 
the international community and return as a responsible member 
of the world community," the statement said. 

</TEXT>

