<H3> <TI>   U.S., Seoul Officials Inspect Vessels </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S., Seoul Officials Inspect Vessels </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406091494 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0800 GMT 14 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1406091494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from KBS General Bureau in Pusan] </F>
  [Text] In connection with North Korea's nuclear issue, a 
ROK-U.S. joint inspection has been conducted of a ROK vessel 
that will be mobilized to transport U.S. military supplies in an 
emergency. 
  The inspection was conducted at Point No. 1 of the Central 
Pier of Pusan Harbor on 10 June. It has been confirmed that an 
inspection was conducted of the facilities of the vessel; of the 
procedure to hand over the vessel in an emergency; and of the 
status of the fuel storage of No. 9 Donam, a 4,998 tonne-class 
cargo vessel belonging to the Hung-A Maritime Company. 
  An official concerned at Pusan Harbor said: As South-North 
relations have recently become tense, I understand an inspection 
has been conducted of a vessel that will be mobilized in an 
emergency. In an emergency, several vessels, including tankers 
and passenger ships--besides the aforementioned vessel--will be 
handed over to the U.S. Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

