<H3> <TI>   U.S., ROK, Japanese Present `Nuclear Threat' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S., ROK, Japanese Present `Nuclear Threat' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406103594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1027 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406103594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Total Removal of Nuclear Threat is Vital to </F>
Denuclearization of Korean Peninsula" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- If the Korean peninsula 
is to be denuclearized, the nuclear threat must be totally 
eliminated from this region, declares NODONG SINMUN in a 
by-lined article today. 
  Eliminating the nuclear threat on the Korean peninsula 
means, 
in essence, removing the U.S. nuclear threat and putting an end 
to the nuclear armament of Japan and the South Korean puppets, 
the article says, and continues: 
  What should be done first of all for the denuclearization of 
the Korean peninsula is to terminate the U.S. nuclear threat. 
The elimination of the U.S. nuclear weapons and the removal of 
its nuclear threat on the peninsula are the key to its 
denuclearization. 
  It is also necessary for the denuclearization of the 
peninsula to put a period to Japan's nuclear armament. 
  The nuclear armament of Japan poses a nuclear threat to the 
DPRK and obstructs the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula. 
Putting an end to Japan's nuclear armament is an urgent demand 
arising in the total removal of the nuclear threat in this 
region and the denuclearization of the peninsula. 
  Checking the nuclear arms development by the South Korean 
puppets is also imperative. In actuality, the joint declaration 
on denuclearization has been reduced to a dead letter and the 
denuclearization of the Korean peninsula made impossible by the 
traitor Kim Yong-sam. 
  The nuclear threat by the United States, Japan and the South 
Korean puppets is contrary to the trend of the time. 
  The nuclear threat must be totally removed and the Korean 
peninsula be turned nuclear free. 

</TEXT>

