<H3> <TI>   `Craftiness', `Effrontery' Alleged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Craftiness', `Effrontery' Alleged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0509 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Don't Run Riot"--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- Japanese Prime Minister 
Tsutomu Hata, far from making an official apology for the police 
raid on the Kyoto Headquarters of the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and search of houses of 
Chongnyon officials and other places, blared that "there was 
nothing wrong in the precedures of the search." 
  Commenting on this, NODONG SINMUN today says that this 
revealed once again the craftiness and effrontery peculiar to 
Japan. 
  Recalling that a situation resembling that on the eve of the 
past Korean war has been created in Japan now, the analyst says: 
  The Japanese reactionaries should know clearly what a 
country 
the DPRK is, what a people the Koreans are and how great our 
might is. And they must not doubt the will of our people who 
mean what they say. 
  Should Japan join in "sanctions" against us, whether she 
takes the van or is inveigled into it, we will regard it as a 
declaration of war and then she will not be able to evade a 
deserved punishment. This warning is anything but an empty word. 
The Japanese authorities should ponder over the lot in which 
Japan would find itself, if this warning of ours is carried into 
practice. 
  The Japanese reactionaries must not run riot but promptly 
stop their hostile policy against the DPRK and the repression of 
Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan. This advice is quite beneficial 
to Japan. 

</TEXT>

