<DATE1>  13 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japan's `Suppression' of Chongnyon Protested </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's `Suppression' of Chongnyon Protested </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Pomminnyon Releases Statement </H4>

<F P=102> SK1306055594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0521 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306055594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 13 (KCNA) -- The North side 
headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's 
Reunification (Pomminnyon) released a statement on June 12. 
  It warns: 
  "If the Japanese authorities continue their acts of 
deliberately aggravating the situation, taking advantage of the 
vicious pressure campaign of the United States and the South 
Korean authorities against the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea, in disregard of the demand of our nation, they will be 
held responsible for the consequences arising therefrom." 
  "The raid on the Kyoto prefectural headquarters of the 
General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) was 
a fascist outrage against Koreans overseas and an unpardonable 
political suppression," the statement says, and goes on: 
  "We cannot but call in question the fact that all the 
hostile 
acts persistently committed by the Japanese authorities against 
Chongnyon are timed to coincide with the anti-DPRK campaign of 
the United States and the South Korean authorities. 
  "The Koreans residing in Japan are mostly victims who were 
taken there as `labor draftees' for the Japanese imperialists' 
war of aggression on the continent and forced to toils, 
undergoing all manner of national humiliation and harsh 
maltreatment in the past, and their descendants. 
  "Nevertheless, the Japanese authorities, far from repenting 
of this and making compensations, are repeating the past crimes 
today. This naturally arouses the resentment of the whole nation. 
  "The North side headquarters of Pomminnyon can hardly 
repress 
indignation at the surprise raid on and search of Chongnyon 
organisations by the Japanese police and strongly urge the 
Japanese authorities to immediately stop such criminal 
suppression and apologize for it and punish those responsible 
for it." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

