<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japanese `Design' `To Dominate Asia' Alleged </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japanese `Design' `To Dominate Asia' Alleged </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406101294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1003 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406101294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["NODONG SINMUN on Reinvasion Moves of Japanese Militarism" </F>
-- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The Japanese 
reactionaries are now zealously joining the United States in its 
policy of stifling the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, 
fully revealing the wild ambition of revived militarism for 
reinvasion, says NODONG SINMUN in a commentary today. 
  The Japanese reactionaries are going ahead with legislative 
arrangements to quickly send "Self-Defense Forces" to the Korean 
peninsula in "the event of contingency," declaring that they 
will take an active part in "collective security measures" in 
case "sanctions" were taken against the DPRK, the analyst says, 
and continues: 
  They are crying over the DPRK's "nuclear threat" so 
hysterically for the purpose of converting Japan into a military 
power equipped with nuclear weapons under that pretext and 
realising with the backing of the United States the old dream of 
"the greater east Asia coprosperity sphere" which Japan failed 
to do in the past. 
  To dominate Asia is the invariable design of the Japanese 
reactionaries. It is to this end that they are now making haste 
with the conversion of Japan into a military power and her 
nuclear armament. They intend to divert the worldwide 
denunciation elsewhere from Japan and justify their moves to 
turn Japan into a military power armed with nuclear weapons by 
widely spreading the rumor about the DPRK's "nuclear threat." 
  They are also scheming to stage a comeback to Korea and 
other 
Asian nations by actively partaking of the aggressive military 
actions of the United States. 
  The peace and security of Northeast Asia and the 
Asian-Pacific region are gravely threatened by Japan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

