<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chuche Idea Seminar Held in Japan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chuche Idea Seminar Held in Japan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0306112294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1007 GMT 3 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0306112294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 1 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- A 
seminar on the chuche idea was held recently in Sanda, Hyogo 
prefecture, under the co- sponsorship of the societies for the 
study of Kim Chong-il's works in Kansai district, Japan. 
  Lectures on the subjects "On ideological and theoretical 
achievements of secretary Kim Chong-il" and "Chuche-based view 
of life" were given at the seminar. 
  Masaji Ie, chief advisor to the Japan Liaison Council of 
Societies for the Study of Kim Chong-il's Works and professor at 
the Kobe University of Foreign Studies, elaborated on the great 
ideological and theoretical achievements of the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il in developing in depth the immortal chuche 
idea founded by the respected leader President Kim Il-song. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

