<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cuba Calls For Negotiated Solution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cuba Calls For Negotiated Solution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1006102194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1000 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1006102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- A solidarity letter 
came from Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina Gonzalez hoping 
that the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula will be resolved 
peacefully through negotiations, not by pressure and strong-arm 
action. 
  Charging that the United States of America is getting 
overheated in further arming South Korea, while increasing 
international pressure on the Democratic People's Republic of 
Korea, he reaffirmed the opinion that a reasonable solution in 
face of the explosive situation of the Korean peninsula is not a 
military option but negotiation. 
  He, on behalf of the Cuban Government and people, expressed 
the belief that the strain will surely be eased and the most 
reasonable way be opened for the DPRK Government and people in 
the solution to the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

