<H3> <TI>   Philippine President Remarks on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Philippine President Remarks on Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1006053194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0443 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1006053194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["`actions Against North Korea Could Bring the Korean </F>
Peninsula Down the Road to Conflict': Philippine President" -- 
KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Philippine President 
Fidel Ramos at his weekly press conference on June 8 called for 
the avoidance of actions against North Korea that might provoke 
a confrontation, which he said in turn could bring the region 
down the road to conflict, according to a XINHUA report. 
  The president reiterated the Philippine policy on North 
Korea's "nuclear issue" that has been to urge patient 
consultation and creative diplomacy in the search for a solution. 
  He said "the Philippines hope that a peaceful solution could 
still be found to resolve the issue." 

</TEXT>

