<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   SRV `High-Level' Military Delegation Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SRV `High-Level' Military Delegation Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406152694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1519 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406152694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- A high-level military 
delegation of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam arrived here by 
air today. 
  The delegation led by General Doan Khue, Politburo member of 
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam and 
minister of national defence, consists of Lt. Gen. Phan Thu, 
vice-minister of national defence; Lt. Gen. Le Hai, deputy head 
of the General Political Department of the Vietnam People's 
Army; Lt. Gen. Tran Hanh, deputy chief of the General Staff of 
the Vietnam People's Army, and other members. 
  It was met at the airport by O Chin-u, member of the 
Presidium of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of 
the Workers' Party of Korea and minister of People's Armed 
Forces; Vice Marshal of the Korean People's Army Kim Kwang-chin; 
Col. Gen. Pak Chae-kyong; Lt. Gen. Pak Sung-won and other 
generals and officers of the Korean People's Army. 
  Vietnamese Ambassador to Korea Duong Chinh Thuc was also 
present there to meet the delegation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

