<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Yong-nam Meets Leaders From Iran, India </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Yong-nam Meets Leaders From Iran, India </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1006045194 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0500 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1006045194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 0500 GMT 7 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kim Yong-nam, vice premier and foreign minister, 
who was in Egypt, met with the Iranian foreign minister, the 
Guinean minister of foreign affairs and cooperation, the 
Tanzanian minister of foreign affairs and international 
cooperation, and the Indian state minister of external affairs 
on 2 and 3 June. 
  On these occasions, the foreign minister extended greetings 
from the great leader Comrade Kim Il-song and the dear leader 
Comrade Kim Chong-il to Indian President Shankar Dayal Sharma, 
Indian Prime Minister P. V. Narasimha Rao, Iranian Islam leader 
Sayed 'Ali Khamene'i, Iranian President Akbar 
Hashemi-Rafsanjani, Guinean President Lansana Conte, and 
Tanzanian President Ali Hassan Mwinyi. 
  The foreign ministers expressed deep appreciation for this 
and asked our country's foreign minister to extend greetings 
from the head of state and government of each country to the 
great leader Comrade Kim Il-song and the dear leader Comrade Kim 
Chong-il. Conversations took place in a friendly atmosphere. 
  The foreign minister also met with the minister of foreign 
relations. 
  Previously, on 1 June, the foreign minister met with 
Indonesian President Suharto's adviser in charge of the 
Nonaligned Movement and talked with him. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

