<H3> <TI>   Pyongyang Papers Observe Day of Portugal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pyongyang Papers Observe Day of Portugal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1006103994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1009 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1006103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Day of Portugal Observed" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Papers here today 
observe the day of Portugal. 
  The Korean people wish the Portuguese people greater 
achievements in their endeavors for the prosperity and 
development of the country, MINJU CHOSON in a signed article 
says, and goes on: 
  The Korean and Portuguese peoples have established bonds of 
friendship. The friendly and cooperative relations have grown 
stronger and developed after the two countries established 
diplomatic ties at ambassadorial level in April 1975. 
  The Korean people believe that the relations between the two 
peoples will develop still further in the future, too, on the 
basis of the idea of independence, peace and friendship. 

</TEXT>

