<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kim Chong-il Works Studied in Various Countries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kim Chong-il Works Studied in Various Countries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1206101694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0803 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1206101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the work 
of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il "Our Socialism Centred 
on the Masses Shall Not Perish" was held by the Dar-es-Salaam, 
Tanzania, association for the study of the chuche idea. 
  The speakers said that the advantages and vitality of 
Korean-style peculiar socialism centred on the popular masses 
have been fully displayed in all fields and that the socialist 
system of Korea is a genuine popular one which provides the 
masses of the people with an independent and creative life. 
  A reading session of this work was held by the Zairean 
Society for the Study of Kim Chong-il's Works. 
  The speaker said Korean-style socialism is a socialism 
centred on the popular masses where they are the masters of 
everything and everything serves them. They noted that since 
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has always adhered to 
the independent stand, it has been able to defend the national 
dignity and successfully carry on the cause of socialism in any 
storm and stress. 
  A seminar on the work "Abuses of Socialism Are Intolerable" 
took place at the department of the state in charge of 
irrigation of the Ministry of Agriculture of Mozambique. 
  The speakers said the work is a great textbook of revolution 
that gives a scientific exposition of the unavoidableness of the 
downfall of imperialism and the inevitability of the triumph of 
socialism. 
  Noting that though the imperialists are trying to destroy 
Korean socialism, it is a daydream, they stressed that nobody 
can match the Korean people united closely around their leader 
and their party. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

