  [Text] Tokyo, June 14 KYODO -- Japan and the United States 
will hold vice ministerial-level meetings on the bilateral trade 
framework talks on June 22 and 23 in Tokyo, Foreign Ministry 
sources said Tuesday [14 June]. 
  Deputy U.S. Trade Representative Charlene Barshevsky will 
arrive in Japan on June 21 to attend the meeting with Deputy 
Foreign Minister Sadayuki Hayashi, the sources said. 
  Prior to the meeting, working-level talks on 
telecommunications equipment will be held on June 16 and 17 and 
medical equipment talks will be held on June 21 and 22, both in 
Tokyo, the sources said. Since agreeing to resume the stalled 
framework talks, Japan and the U.S. have held working-level 
talks on telecommunications equipment and medical equipment 
earlier this month, reporting some progress. 

