<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Stop Acting Recklessly"--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- At "a meeting of the 
National Security Council" on June 8, the traitor Kim Yong-sam, 
talking about "damage" of the "North's nuclear transparency", 
said "sanctions of the international community is inevitable" 
and pressed home the need to "promote sanctions against the 
North". 
  Commenting on this, a NODONG SINMUN analyst today says: 
  Kim Yong-sam, who had incited North-South confrontation with 
the bellicose remarks that "a military reaction will not be 
ruled out" over the North's "nuclear issue", is now displaying 
feverish activities for "sanctions against the North" in a bid 
to harm the fellow countrymen by joining hands with outside 
forces. This shows that Kim Yong-sam's is a group of traitors 
who have no regard for the country and the nation, for peace and 
peaceful reunification of the country. 
  It is the height of folly for Kim Yong-sam to think he can 
go 
scotfree after getting "sanctions" taken against the fellow 
countrymen through conspiracy with outside forces. 
  The Kim Yong-sam group's attempt to do harm to the fellow 
countrymen, dancing to the tune of outside forces without 
independence, is an act of self-destruction that reminds us of a 
rabid dog barking into the sky, without any knowledge of its 
imminent death. 
  The Kim Yong-sam puppet clique must stop acting rashly, 
clearly mindful that neither Uncle Sam nor Patriot missiles can 
protect them. 
  A MINJU CHOSON analyst warns that the traitor Kim Yong-sam 
should not babble about "sanctions" like a mad dog barking at 
the moon, not knowing its doom, but ponder over the consequences 
that would arise therefrom and stop acting rashly. 

</TEXT>

