<H3> <TI>   NODONG SINMUN Views Christopher-Kozyrev Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NODONG SINMUN Views Christopher-Kozyrev Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506104094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1026 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["`Sanctions' and Dialogue are Incompatible" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 15 (KCNA) -- U.S. Secretary of State 
Christopher and Russian Foreign Minister Kozyrev on June 10 in a 
joint press conference concerning the talks in Turkzy made 
public that the United States and Russia agreed on submitting to 
the UN Security Council a joint resolution envisaging a 
convocation of an international meeting on the security and 
denuclearization of the Korean peninsula while applying 
"sanctions" to the DPRK, according to a report. 
  NODONG SINMUN today says this shows that the moves to 
isolate 
and stifle the DPRK are expanding, assuming a new aspect in the 
international arena. 
  The news analyst goes on: 
  It is not to be thought of to convene an international 
meeting while applying "sanctions" to us. "Sanctions" and 
dialogue are incompatible. 
  We expressed some concern over the Russia-proposed 
international meeting, proceeding from the hope that it may 
make an affirmative contribution to a fair solution of the 
nuclear issue and other matters on the Korean peninsula through 
negotiations after the rupture of the DPRK-U.S. talks. But we 
will never allow any attempt to make the international meeting a 
lever of pressure on us. 
  We have made it clear that in case any "sanction" is applied 
to us, the parties joining it whether it is at their own will 
or against their will, and the parties backing it, would take 
the responsibility for this. This is not an empty talk. 
  We are ready to solve the matter through dialogue and 
negotiations but we will strongly counter pressure and 
"sanctions" against us. 

</TEXT>

