<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Ugly Outpourings of Traitor" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong-sam the 
traitor, when he met ex-President of the U.S. Jimmy Carter 
visiting South Korea Tuesday, again let out a string of rubbish 
about the "inevitability of UN sanctions against the North," 
driveling that the withdrawal of the North from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] is "something 
abnormal" and "a downright challenge to the demand of the 
international community," according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  At a press conference after meeting Carter that day, the 
puppet Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu cried that "the UN Security 
Council will take a determined measure, should the North fail to 
change its attitude." 
  The puppets used a profusion of ugly words to bring their 
sinister intention against the North home to Carter on the eve 
of his visit to the North. 
  Kim Yong-sam the traitor even asked Carter to "particularly 
guard against the smiling strategy of the North" while visiting 
it, unable to conceal his extreme uneasiness and irritation. 
  This made it plain that the traitor was secretly vexed by 
Carter's visit to Pyongyang. 
  Kim Yong-sam's hysteric outcry that the North's withdrawal 
from the IAEA is "something abnormal" was a ridiculous jargon. 
His hue and cry was, in the final analysis, a mean trash for 
evading responsibility for the criminal act in having driven the 
situation to a catastrophic phase by joining hands with the 
United States and some quarters of the IAEA Secretariat in the 
adoption of a "resolution" to stifle the DPRK. By insisting on 
the "inevitability of UN sanctions" the traitor Kim Yong-sam 
fully revealed the real intention of the South Korean puppet 
clique to isolate and stifle the North at any cost by laying 
obstacles in the way of DPRK-U.S. talks all along. 

</TEXT>

