<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Activities of Overseas Koreans </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports Activities of Overseas Koreans </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106020294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1504 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106020294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Koreans' organisations 
and Koreans in Americas and Europe are briskly conducting 
activities to make this year a year of the great unity of the 
nation. 
  The American Committee on the Korean Question repeatedly 
published informations supporting the 10-point programme of the 
great unity of the whole nation in December last year and early 
this year. 
  The informations said the 10-point programme is the most 
fair 
and aboveboard proposal of reunification acceptable to anyone 
irrespective of differences in ideology and idea, party 
affiliation and religious belief. 
  The One Korea Movement in a statement said the 10-point 
programme indicates the way of ending the national division, 
promoting the national interests and achieving security and 
prosperity of the Korean nation. 
  Son Hak-won, chairman of the Society for the Study of the 
Chuche Idea of Koreans in the United States, in his address to a 
meeting held in Los Angeles in April to celebrate the birthday 
of the great leader President Kim Il-song, called on overseas 
compatriots to build an independent, democratic, neutral and 
denuclearized country by following the spirit of the great 
national unity of President Kim Il-song. 
  A meeting for achieving Korea's reunification under the 
banner of the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole 
nation also was held in Washington in April, and the 3rd meeting 
of the Society for Peaceful Reunification of Korea took place in 
Berkeley, the United States. 
  Organisations of Koreans overseas are briskly conducting 
activities to explain and disseminate the 10-point programme of 
the great unity of the whole nation. 
  Organizations of Koreans in Germany published and 
distributed 
to compatriots the "10-Point Programme of the Great Unity of the 
Whole Nation for the Reunification of the Country" and books 
explaining the programme, including "Great Charter of National 
Unity" and "New Evolution of Principles of National 
Reunification." 

</TEXT>

