<H3> <TI>   Hanminjon Favors Elimination of Nuclear Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hanminjon Favors Elimination of Nuclear Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406105594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1012 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The Central Committee 
of the South Korean National Democratic Front (Hanminjon) in a 
letter to the international environmental organization 
Greenpeace supported its call for the total elimination of 
nuclear weapons, the Seoul-based Radio Voice of National 
Salvation reported. 
  Noting that the universal elimination of nuclear weapons 
must 
be realized at an early date for peace of mankind, the letter 
said: 
  To this end, the United States, "a chief nuclear culprit" 
which was the first in the world to develop and use nuclear 
weapons and, at present, has the largest number of them, must 
eliminate its nuclear weapons first and, for the present, 
withdraw all its nuclear weapons from South Korea and Northeast 
Asia. 
  The international reactionary forces including the United 
States must give up their dirty nuclear intrigue against the 
North, and the nuclear armament of South Korea and the Japanese 
authorities being promoted with their tacit approval must be 
stopped at once. 
  The letter said Hanminjon will always merge its voice of 
justice with the Greenpeace in active response to its just 
initiative and appeal and make all efforts to expand the 
movement for their realization everywhere Hanminjon is present 
and to all the governments, political parties and organizations 
with which it has contact. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

