<F P=102>   SK1106104694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1016 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106104694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
National Council of Representatives of Trade Unions (Chonnodae) 
at a press conference on June 8 declared that should railway 
workers go on strike, all the workers affiliated with it would 
take joint action, according to a radio report from Seoul. 
  It also said it will take joint action in all work places of 
its affiliates all at once if its demand, such as the withdrawal 
of the proposed wage hike this year which was set by the 
"government"-subsidized "federation of trade unions," bowing to 
the authorities, and the reinstatement of dismissed workers, is 
not met. 

