<H3> <TI>   Jun Resistance Anniversary Commemorated in Seoul </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Jun Resistance Anniversary Commemorated in Seoul </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1206102794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0821 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1206102794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- Members of the National 
Alliance for Democracy and Reunification (Chongukyonhap) and the 
South Korean Federation of General Student Councils 
(Hanchongnyon), more than 4,000 in all, held an all-people 
memorial service for those who fell while fighting for the 
nation and democracy at the amphitheatre of the Hanyang 
University on June 11, a Seoul-based radio reported. 
  In his opening address, Yi Chang-pok, permanent chairman of 
Chongukyonhap, charged that "the present Kim Yong-sam 
`government' is totally blocking democratisation and 
reunification" and called for an all-people movement to check 
"the parliamentary ratification of the final act of the Uruguay 
Round world trade accord" and demanded a peaceful solution to 
the nuclear issue of the Korean peninsula. 
  Then, a rally marking the June resistance anniversary was 
held to inherit the spirit of the martyrs. 
  The ralliers vowed to fulfil the tasks to realise a genuine 
democracy and independent reunification on the occasion of the 
7th anniversary of the resistance. 

</TEXT>

