<H3> <TI>   Delegation of Japanese Socialists on Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation of Japanese Socialists on Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Further Inter-Party Talks Held </H4>

<F P=102> SK1306055194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0450 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306055194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 13 (KCNA) -- Talks between 
delegations of the Workers' Party of Korea and the Japan 
Social-Democratic Party (JSDP) were held here Sunday. 
  Present at the talks on the Korean side were vice department 
director of the C.C., the WPK Kim Yang-kon and other officials 
concerned and on the Japanese side were the members of the 
delegation led by director of the General Affairs Department of 
the Central Executive Committee of the JSDP and member of the 
House of Representatives Kazo Watanabe. 
  At the talks the Korean side said the Japanese authorities 
must renounce the hostile policy against the DPRK and solve the 
DPRK-Japan relations in the spirit of the three-party joint 
declaration and clarified the principled stand of the DPRK 
toward the nuclear issue. 
  The Japanese side said it is the JSDP's stand to always 
develop friendly relations with the WPK and strive for peace and 
security in Asia. 
  It also stressed that the "nuclear issue" of Korea should be 
solved peacefully through dialogue and negotiation, not 
"sanctions" and pressure. 

</TEXT>

