<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Koreans in Japan Denounce Suppression of Chongnyon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Koreans in Japan Denounce Suppression of Chongnyon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406105394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1008 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406105394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 12 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- A 
Tokyo metropolitan meeting of Koreans in Japan took place on 
June 11 to protest the Japanese authorities' unjustifiable 
suppression of the General Association of Korean Residents in 
Japan (Chongnyon) and national persecution. 
  In his report at the meeting Pae Pyong-tu, vice-chairman of 
the Chongnyon Central Standing Committee and concurrently 
chairman of the Tokyo metropolitan headquarters of Chongnyon, 
condemned the Japanese authorities' suppression of Chongnyon and 
said all the branches, chapters, organizations and enterprises 
of Chongnyon should put spurs on the "each-visit-100 family 
drive" with this meeting as an occasion, going deep among the 
compatriots and uniting them and arousing them to the struggle 
to smash the crackdown on Chongnyon. 
  Nachiko Aoki, vice-chairman of the Tokyo metropolitan 
headquarters of the Japan Social-Democratic Party and member of 
the Tokyo metropolitan assembly, and other Japanese figures in 
their solidarity addresses to the meeting vowed to strive 
actively to eliminate discriminations against Korean residents 
in Japan and prevent a recurrence of human rights abuses in the 
Japan society. 
  Koreans of various strata under the Tokyo metropolitan 
headquarters said in their indignation speeches that they would 
firmly unite with compatriots and turn out as one in the 
struggle to safeguard the socialist homeland of chuche and the 
Chongnyon organization and defend the rights of compatriots 
under the wise guidance of the dear leader Marshal Kim Chong-il. 
  A protest message to the Japanese prime minister was adopted 
at the meeting. 
  Earlier, on June 10, a Kyoto prefectural meeting of Koreans 
in Japan took place to denounce the Japanese authorities' 
political suppression of the Kyoto organization of Chongnyon and 
national persecution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

