<H3> <TI>   Anti-Korean `Rampage' by Osaka Police Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anti-Korean `Rampage' by Osaka Police Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106053994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0441 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106053994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 9 (KNS-KCNA) -- The Osaka prefectural 
police and the Higashi Police Station of Japan are getting all 
the more arrogant, ignoring the strong protest by the Koreans in 
Japan and public opinion at home and abroad, according to CHOSON 
SINBO. 
  The paper said the Osaka prefectural police, far from 
apologizing for its criminal acts, let out a stream of 
provocative words at officials of the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans, shouting 
"Chongnyon of Korea, break up your protest action" and "we will 
arrest you, if you stay any longer". 
  The rampage of the Japanese right-wing gangsters is assuming 
greater intensity, coupled with the arrogance of the Japanese 
police. 
  On the 6th of June, they appeared around the prefectural 
police bureau and the Higashi Police Station where Koreans were 
staging a protest and made a fuss, shouting "away with Koreans." 
  On the 7th, right-wing gangsters belonging to the "League of 
Asian Nations" came with an armoured vehicle and a loudspeaker 
car and threatened Koreans who were staging a protest, uttering 
uncleanly words unfit for human mouth. 
  The suppression by the Japanese reactionaries has lashed the 
Koreans in Japan into fury. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

