<H3> <TI>   Chondoist Group Protests Japanese `Crackdown' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chondoist Group Protests Japanese `Crackdown' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406050194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0423 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406050194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- The Central Guidance 
Committee of the Korean Chondoist Association in a statement 
June 13 strongly urged the Japanese authorities to immediately 
stop their crackdown on the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) and Koreans in Japan and 
apologize for it and punish those responsible for the recent 
criminal acts. 
  "The recent crackdown on the Osaka and Kyoto prefectural 
headquarters of Chongnyon was a fascist outrage designed to 
totally suppress Chongnyon, part of their premeditated anti-DPRK 
moves encouraged by the U.S. manoeuvres to isolate and stifle 
the DPRK over its fictitious `nuclear issue', and a grave 
challenge to the DPRK, an independent and sovereign state," the 
statement says, and goes on: 
  "The Central Guidance Committee of the Korean Chondoist 
Association sternly denounces the Japanese police outrages in 
the name of the entire Chondoists of the DPRK, branding them as 
rash acts of murderers, fascist maniacs to commit a second Kanto 
massacre. 
  "We will consider any suppression of Chongnyon to be an 
encroachment on the dignity and sovereignty of our republic and 
decisively counter it. 
  "If the Japanese authorities persist in their crackdown on 
Chongnyon and Koreans in Japan, they would be held wholly 
responsible for all the consequences arising therefrom." 
  The statement expresses the hope that the South Korean 
Chondoists and Tangun Taejonggyo believers too would turn out in 
the struggle to defend the dignity of their resourceful nation 
and check the Japanese reactionaries' suppression of Koreans in 
Japan. 

</TEXT>

