<H3> <TI>   Japan's Treatment of Chongnyon Criticized Abroad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's Treatment of Chongnyon Criticized Abroad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106111894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1049 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- The Japanese 
authorities' suppression of the General Association of Korean 
Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) is under fire in different 
countries. 
  The Ghanaian National Institute of the Chuche Idea in a 
letter of protest to the Japanese prime minister June 3 said the 
Japanese authorities' search of Chongnyon, a legitimate 
organisation of overseas citizens of the DPRK, with the 
mobilisation of huge police and even their unhesitating murder 
and violence are a politically motivated sinister inhumane act. 
  Noting that this was an anti-human political suppression the 
like of which could hardly be seen in the history of the world, 
the letter demanded that the Japanese authorities immediately 
stop suppressing Chongnyon organisations, apologize for their 
encroachment on the legitimate rights of Koreans in Japan and 
fully guarantee their political rights and freedom regulated 
under the publicly recognized international law. 
  The chairman of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association in a 
letter of protest to the Japanese Government May 31 denounced 
the Japanese authorities for suppressing Chongnyon as part of 
their campaign against the DPRK and stepping up the anti-DPRK 
campaign in league with international reactionaries, and urged 
them to stop it at once. 

</TEXT>

