<H3> <TI>   Resolution on Japan's War Responsibilities Demanded </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Resolution on Japan's War Responsibilities Demanded </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106104494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1010 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106104494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 9 [date as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- 
Prominent figures of Japan including political scientist Takeshi 
Ishida and lawyer Tsukuo Imamura met the speaker of the House of 
Representatives and the chairman of the House of Councillors on 
June 2 and handed them a letter urging the adoption of a special 
Diet resolution on Japan's responsibility for the war and 
apology and the establishment of an ad hoc committee for the 
investigation into postwar compensation. 
  Recalling that many Asian people were killed in Japan's war 
of aggression, they strongly demanded a thoroughgoing 
investigation into the outstanding issue of postwar compensation 
including the forcible drafting of Koreans and the issue of 
"comfort women for the army", the publication of its results and 
the clarification of the responsibility. 
  They said that the Diet should immediately adopt a special 
resolution on the responsibility for the war and apology with 
the approval of both houses and apologize for Japan's past 
crimes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

