<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Defense Minister, Delegation Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Defense Minister, Delegation Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Holds Talks With Military Leaders </H4>

<F P=102> SK1506113794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1108 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506113794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 15 (KCNA) -- A military delegation 
of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea held talks with the 
high-level military delegation of the Socialist Republic of 
Vietnam in Pyongyang today. 
  Present at the talks on the Korean side were O Chin-u, 
member 
of the presidium of the Political Bureau of the C.C. [Central 
Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea and minister of People's 
Armed Forces, Vice Marshal Kim Kwang-chin, Col. Gen. Pak 
Chae-kyong, Lt. Gen. Pak Sung-won and other generals and 
officers of the Korean People's Army. 
  Present on the opposite side were Gen. Doan Khue, Politburo 
member of the C.C., the Communist Party of Vietnam and minister 
of national defence, who is the head of the delegation, and Lt. 
Gen. Phan Thu, vice-minister of national defence, Lt. Gen. Le 
Hai, deputy head of the General Political Department of the 
Vietnam People's Army, Lt. Gen. Tran Hanh, deputy chief of the 
General Staff of the Vietnam People's Army, who are members of 
the delegation and suites and Vietnamese Ambassador to Korea 
Duong Chinh Thuc. 
  The talks proceeded in a friendly atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

