<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indian, Ghanaian Parties Send Solidarity Messages </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Indian, Ghanaian Parties Send Solidarity Messages </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406054294 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0427 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406054294 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- Solidarity messages 
came to the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea 
from Indrajit Gupta, general secretary of the National Council 
of the Communist Party of India, and from the National Standing 
Committee of the National Convention Party of Ghana supporting 
the Korean people's struggle to defend their national dignity 
and the sovereignty of their country. 
  The general secretary of the National Council of the 
Communist Party of India in his message said the council highly 
estimates the DPRK's stand against U.S. pressure and for the 
resumption of talks with the United States to solve the 
"question of nuclear inspection" of the DPRK. 
  The National Standing Committee of the National Convention 
Party of Ghana in its message actively welcomed and supported 
the DPRK's proposal to hold negotiations with the United States 
over the establishment of a new peace arrangement that can 
prevent arms buildup and creditably ensure peace on the Korean 
peninsula. 
  The National Convention Party of Ghana expresses firm 
solidarity for the struggle of the Workers' Party and people of 
Korea to achieve national reunification through a confederacy, 
the message said, and urged the United States to accede to the 
DPRK's negotiation proposal to replace the Korean armistice 
agreement by a peace agreement and to withdraw its troops and 
nuclear weapons from South Korea. 

</TEXT>

