<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Daily Expresses People's Solidarity With Libya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Daily Expresses People's Solidarity With Libya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106105494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1030 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Libya's Will for Independence Against Imperialism" -- KCNA </F>
headline] 
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- The Korean people 
express firm solidarity with the Libyan Arab people in their 
just cause for defending the sovereignty of the country on the 
occasion of the anniversary of the dismantlement of the U.S. 
military bases in Libya, says NODONG SINMUN in a by-lined 
article today. 
  The article says: 
  Through the dismantlement of the U.S. military bases the 
Libyan Arab people showed that the strength of the people who 
value their national dignity and sovereignty of their country is 
tremendous. 
  Today the Libyan Arab people steadfastly maintain the stand 
of independence against imperialism. This enjoys sympathy and 
support of the world progressive people including the African 
people. 
  The imperialists are persisting in their pressure and 
interference against Libya which is advancing along the road of 
independence, regarding it as a thorn in their flesh. But they 
could not break down the will of the Libyan Arab people. 
  The Libyan Arab people are firmly safeguarding their 
national 
dignity and sovereignty of their country under the leadership of 
Colonel Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi, leader of the great September 
first revolution. 

</TEXT>

