<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of Kim Chong-il Guidance Marked </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of Kim Chong-il Guidance Marked </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1306055394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0454 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1306055394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 13 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held 
Sunday to commemorate the 30th anniversary of the on-the-spot 
guidance of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il to the Korean 
Central News Agency. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il guided the KCNA on the spot on June 12, 
1964. 
  He had a historical talk entitled "The Basic Tasks Facing 
the 
Korean Central News Agency" with KCNA officials, clearly 
indicating the road ahead of it. 
  Comrade Kim Chong-il gave flawless answers to all the 
theoretical and practical questions for the development of the 
work of the news agency such as its basic tasks, functions and 
role, the principles it must maintain to become a mighty 
ideological weapon of the party and ways for their application. 
  After his on-the-spot guidance, KCNA has been able to serve 
better for the cause of modelling of the whole society on the 
chuche idea as an ideological weapon of the Workers' Party of 
Korea and defend and exalt the revolutionary tradition of the 
chuche-based press. 
  KCNA has grown to be a collective unfailingly loyal to the 
party and the leader over the past 30 years. 
  Tasks were set forth at the meeting to enhance its functions 
and role in every way as a mouthpiece of the party and the 
government. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

