<H3> <TI>   Chang Chol Speaks at Film Week Premiere </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chang Chol Speaks at Film Week Premiere </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1406045694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0435 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1406045694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 14 (KCNA) -- A film week began from 
June 13 to mark the 30th anniversary of the start of work by the 
dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il at the Central Committee of the 
Workers' Party of Korea. 
  During the film week all the cinema houses across the 
country 
will screen many documentary films including "Great Guidance 
Leading Our Party Always to Victories," "Great Leadership 
Glorifying Revolutionary Traditions Through Ages," "Korea, I 
Will Glorify Thee," and "The Great Paragon," which record the 
feats of the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il in his leadership. 
  The feature films "Guarantee" (Part one and two,) "The Looks 
of a Party Member" and "Story About a Flower" and the multi-part 
feature film "The Nation and Destiny" will be screened during 
the week. 
  The opening ceremony of the film week took place at the 
Kaeson Cinema House in Pyongyang Monday. 
  An opening address was made by Vice Premier of the 
Administration Council and Minister of Culture and Art Chang 
Chol. 

</TEXT>

