<H3> <TI>   Seminar Held by `Pressmen' in Pyongyang </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seminar Held by `Pressmen' in Pyongyang </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106053794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0437 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106053794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 11 (KCNA) -- A seminar of pressmen 
took place in Pyongyang on the lapse of 30 years since the dear 
leader Comrade Kim Chong-il began to work in the Central 
Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
  The speakers said the dear leader, with a deep insight into 
the great role of news media in the revolutionary struggle, has 
attached particular importance to the publication and 
information services and led them since he began his work in the 
party Central Committee. 
  They said the undying feats performed by him in guiding the 
publication and information services are that he provided a 
great guideline for the building of revolutionary news media of 
the working class by putting forward a chuche-based idea and 
theories on the publication and information services, kindled 
the flames of revolutionization of newspapers, news services and 
publications and established a revolutionary work system of the 
press media. 
  They pointed out that at a time when news media of some 
countries have been reduced to guides on the frustration of 
socialism and their return to capitalism, giving in to the 
bourgeois ideological offensive of the imperialists and 
reactionaries, the news media of the DPRK are serving as 
triumphant drumbeats in the noble struggle to resolutely defend 
the party and the leader and safeguard and glorify the socialist 
bastion under the banner of the chuche idea. They added that 
this is entirely results of the wise guidance of the dear leader 
who put forward a great chuche-based programme of the press and 
led the struggle to carry it into reality. 

</TEXT>

