<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Seminar Held in Pyongyang on Literature, Art </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1206102194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0825 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1206102194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 12 (KCNA) -- A seminar of literary 
men and artistes was held here on the lapse of 30 years since 
the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il began to work at the 
Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. 
  Speakers said Korea has met a great heyday of literature and 
art thanks to the chuche-based literary and art thought and 
energetic guidance of the dear leader. They noted that with a 
revolutionary change in film, opera, drama and all other domains 
of literature and art, immortal classical masterpieces were 
adapted in various art forms and the theoretical and practical 
problems arising in creation and representation including the 
portrayal of the leader in literary and art works were 
successfully solved. 
