<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Increase in Salt Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports Increase in Salt Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1106020394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1506 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1106020394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 10 (KCNA) -- Salt production is 
increasing in Korea. At salt works of the country the salt 
production in four months of this year increased more than 20 
percent compared with the same period of last year. 
  The Yonbaek Salt Works which began the production of salt 
one 
week earlier than last year has overfulfilled its monthly quotas 
by 47 percent on an average by actively introducing advanced 
production methods. 
  The Kwangyangman salt works has produced several thousand 
more tons of salt in this period. 
  Kuisong and Namyang salt works which fulfilled their may 
plans respectively at 102 and 105 percent are carrying out their 
daily salt production this month at more than 130 percent. 
  The salt works across the country are exerting all their 
efforts to attain the goal of increasing production for this 
month 50 percent as against last month. 

</TEXT>

