<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on North Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Comments on North Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Urges World To Be Careful </H4>

<F P=102> BK1306054094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 
13 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1306054094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Australian foreign minister, Senator Gareth 
Evans, has urged the United Nations Security Council to be 
careful about any decision directed at North Korea. Speaking in 
Manila, Senator Evans said the situation needs to be handled 
delicately. Trevor Watson reports. 
  [Begin Watson recording] Senator Evans said he would deplore 
any decision that drives the North Koreans beyond the point of 
no return in their dealings with the International Atomic Energy 
Agency or the world community. Nobody, he said, knows if 
sanctions will do that or encourage the North to be more open in 
the future. 
  [Evans] Will it serve the purpose of keeping them committed 
in the future to ensure that we at least know there won't be 
diversion of nuclear material in the future, or we would be the 
trigger which in fact pushes them over the brink to walk away 
from the non-proliferation treaty all together. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

