<F P=100> AUSTRALASIA </F>
<F P=101> Australia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Employment Minister Begins Asian Tour </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Employment Minister Begins Asian Tour </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1206113194 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 1100 GMT 
12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1206113194 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia's employment minister, Simon Crean, 
arrives in Vietnam shortly on the first leg of a trip to Asia 
aimed at strengthening trade links with the region. 
  In Hanoi, Mr. Crean will sign a memorandum of understanding 
with the government as the first step in Australian business 
setting up cooperative projects providing high quality education 
and training. And in Indonesia, Mr. Crean will be part of 
Australia's largest ever trade and cultural promotion in the 
region. 
  During his Malaysian stopover, Mr. Crean will meet senior 
officials to discuss priority areas for cooperation in 
vocational education and training. 

</TEXT>

