<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Circular on Export Procedure Changes Issued </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Circular on Export Procedure Changes Issued </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1406091194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1100 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1406091194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Trade recently issued a circular 
which announces that effective from 1 July, the procedure of 
issuing export permits for a single trip will be abolished 
except in the following cases: 
  -- Goods that are banned from export; 
  -- Goods exported according to special plans; 
  -- Goods of specifically managed industries; 
  -- Special cases: goods for exchanging, semi-export 
goods, goods intended for labor-intensive produce exhibitions, 
and goods produced by foreign enterprises in Vietnam. 
  Before the date this circular becomes effective nationwide, 
the Ministry of Trade and the Customs General Department will 
select a number of localities and production establishments 
which will experiment with the new procedures immediately in 
June. The circular will become effective nationwide on 1 July. 
  The cancellation of the procedure of issuing export permits 
for a single trip will benefit business establishments in their 
export activities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

