<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputy Prime Minister Meets Head of IFC </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputy Prime Minister Meets Head of IFC </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306162594 Hanoi VNA in English 1511 GMT 13 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK1306162594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi VNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi VNA June 13 -- Deputy Prime Minister Tran Duc 
Luong received here today a delegation of the International 
Financial Company (IFC) led by Varel Freeman, head of the 
company's Department for Asia, the Pacific. 
  Speaking to his guests Mr Tran Duc Luong reaffirmed the 
Vietnamese Government highly valued IFC's contribution and 
considered the expansion of its relations with IFC as well as 
other international monetary organisations very important. With 
its open door policy, the Vietnamese Government is pleased to 
create conditions for private companies to invest in Vietnam and 
hoped that IFC would help Vietnam by granting investment credits. 
  For his part, Mr Freeman said that IFC would invest its 
capital in projects prepared by IFC. After investing in the 
first project, IFC will invest in a harbour of Vietnam 
specializing in farm products export and goods import. 
  Over the past three years IFC has sent many delegations to 
Vietnam to define investment projects and joint ventures in 
Vietnam. IFC has also decided to invest in a project on 
expanding Metropole Hotel. 
  At present, IFC is inquiring into the possibilities of 
investing in tourism, cement production and in pipe line 
installation. IFC is also planning a joint venture project with 
Vietnam to set up insurance companies and help Vietnam making 
legal documents relating to stock market activities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

