<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry, UNHCR Review Repatriation Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry, UNHCR Review Repatriation Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1306111194 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1306111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Labor, War Invalids, and Social 
Welfare and the UNHCR [UN High Commissioner for Refugees] held a 
joint conference in Haiphong on 10-11 June to review the task of 
receiving and reintegrating repatriated Vietnamese during the 
1989-94 period. 
  During the past five years, more than 62,000 Vietnamese were 
repatriated from Hong Kong, Thailand, Indonesia, Malaysia, and 
Japan. 
  The Vietnamese Government and international organizations 
have provided aid and assistance to these returnees while 
creating conditions for them to stabilize their daily life and 
to reintegrate themselves quickly into the Vietnamese community. 
  In Haiphong, Quang Ninh, Ho Chi Minh City, Thua Thien-Hue, 
and Quang Nam-Danang about 70-75 percent of the returnees now 
enjoy a relatively stable life, 5-10 percent are doing well, and 
10-15 percent experience difficulty in finding jobs and living 
quarters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

