<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN: Panmunjom Tours Suspended for Renovations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN: Panmunjom Tours Suspended for Renovations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506010694 Seoul THE KOREA HERALD in English 15 Jun 94 p 3 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506010694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul THE KOREA HERALD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tourist trips to the truce village of Panmunjom 
have been suspended this week because of repair work at a 
briefing room for tourists at the truce village, a UN Command 
(UNC) spokesman said yesterday. The spokesman said the 
suspension of trips has nothing to do with the tension fueled by 
the North Korean nuclear program. 
  "The briefing room for tourists who come to see Panmunjom 
and 
nearby underground tunnels dug by North Koreans is very old and 
we need to repair it," said Kim Yong-kyu of the UNC. "That's 
why tours to Panmunjom have been temporarily suspended. They 
will resume Monday," said Kim. He denied a news report that the 
suspension of the trips was related to the existing tensions. 

</TEXT>

