<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group Urges U.S. Not To Foment `War Atmosphere' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group Urges U.S. Not To Foment `War Atmosphere' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1506115094 Seoul YONHAP in English 0932 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1506115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 15 (YONHAP) -- The Citizens Coalition 
for Economic Justice on Wednesday asked the United States to 
stop making acts of fomenting a "war atmosphere" on the Korean 
peninsula for the sake of its own national interests. 
  In a statement it issued in connection with the North Korean 
nuclear question, the coalition stressed that the Untied States 
should refrain from making provocative remarks such as "military 
sanctions being considered." 
  "In particular, the United States should not take any 
military actions that could be regarded by North Korea as the 
provocation of a war," it said. 
  Emphasizing that no fratricidal war should recur between the 
same people, the coalition said the South Korean Government 
should display the intent of resolving the matter through 
dialogue while North Korea should ensure nuclear transparency 
under the basic South-North agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

