<H3> <TI>   Former U.S. President Carter Visits ROK, DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former U.S. President Carter Visits ROK, DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Carter Meets Unification Minister </H4>

<F P=102> SK1506013994 Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network in Korean 0100 GMT 15 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK1506013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul KBS-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yi Hong-ku, deputy prime minister in charge of 
unification, had a breakfast meeting with former U.S. President 
Carter, who is visiting the ROK, and was briefed by President 
Carter regarding his planned activities in North Korea. Deputy 
Prime Minister Yi Hong-ku reportedly asked President Carter to 
exert efforts to enable North Korea to clear up nuclear 
suspicions and join in the international community. 
  Former President Carter will visit North Korea from 15 to 18 
June and will have talks with North Korean President Kim Il-song 
and others. 

</TEXT>

